---
import Docs from "~/layouts/Docs.astro";
import { Code } from "astro:components";
import { howToSchema } from "~/lib/structured-data";
import { SITE_URL } from "~/lib/og";

const pageUrl = `${SITE_URL}/docs/quickstart/`;

const howTo = howToSchema({
  name: "Install Ashlr Stack and provision Supabase",
  description:
    "From a fresh terminal to a provisioned Supabase project with MCP wired into Claude Code.",
  totalTime: "PT5M",
  url: pageUrl,
  steps: [
    {
      name: "Install Stack",
      text: "Install the @ashlr/stack CLI via curl, bun, npm, or Homebrew so the `stack` binary is on your PATH.",
      url: `${pageUrl}#1-install-stack`,
    },
    {
      name: "Verify the install",
      text: "Run `stack status` to confirm the CLI is reachable and Phantom is detected.",
      url: `${pageUrl}#2-verify-the-install`,
    },
    {
      name: "Initialise a project",
      text: "Run `stack init` inside your repo to write .stack.toml (committed) and .stack.local.toml (gitignored).",
      url: `${pageUrl}#3-initialise-a-project`,
    },
    {
      name: "Add your first service",
      text: "Run `stack add supabase` to provision a Supabase project, store secrets in Phantom, and wire .mcp.json.",
      url: `${pageUrl}#4-add-your-first-service`,
    },
    {
      name: "Sanity-check with doctor",
      text: "Run `stack doctor` to verify every provider is reachable and its stored credentials are still valid.",
      url: `${pageUrl}#5-sanity-check-with-doctor`,
    },
    {
      name: "Run your app with secrets injected",
      text: "Run your dev server via `stack exec -- bun dev` so Phantom resolves phm_ tokens to real secret values at spawn.",
      url: `${pageUrl}#6-run-your-app-with-secrets-injected`,
    },
  ],
});
---

<Docs
  title="Quickstart"
  description="From a fresh terminal to a provisioned Supabase project with MCP wired into Claude Code — in about five minutes."
  eyebrow="Getting started"
  extraSchemas={[howTo]}
>
  <h2>Before you start</h2>
  <p>
    Stack is a thin orchestration layer; two other things do the heavy lifting
    and must be on your PATH:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong><a href="/docs/phantom/">Phantom Secrets</a></strong> — holds every
      secret. Stack refuses to run <code>stack add</code> without it.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Node 20+</strong> or <strong>Bun 1.1+</strong> — for the CLI itself
      and for the MCP <code>npx</code> shims certain providers wire up.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>1. Install Stack</h2>
  <p>One-liner:</p>

  <Code
    code={`curl -fsSL stack.ashlr.ai/install.sh | bash`}
    lang="bash"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <p>Or via your package manager:</p>

  <Code
    code={`bun add -g @ashlr/stack
# or
npm i -g @ashlr/stack
# or (macOS)
brew install ashlrai/stack/stack`}
    lang="bash"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <p>And Phantom (required for anything that touches secrets):</p>

  <Code
    code={`brew install ashlrai/phantom/phantom
# or
npm i -g phantom-secrets`}
    lang="bash"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <h2>2. Verify the install</h2>

  <Code
    code={`stack status`}
    lang="bash"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <p>You should see something like:</p>

  <Code
    code={`  Ashlr Stack

  ● .stack.toml       missing — run \`stack init\`
  ● phantom           0 secrets in vault
  ● services          0 configured`}
    lang="text"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <p>
    Two red dots — that's fine. We haven't initialised anything yet. Phantom
    showing a green dot means Stack can talk to the vault.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Initialise a project</h2>
  <p>Inside any repo (Next.js, Astro, Rails, whatever):</p>

  <Code
    code={`cd path/to/your-app
stack init`}
    lang="bash"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <p>
    Stack prompts for a starter template. Pick <strong>blank</strong> for now —
    we'll add services one at a time. Output:
  </p>

  <Code
    code={`┌  stack init
│
◇  Pick a starter template (or blank):
│  Blank — add services later with \`stack add\`
│
└  Wrote .stack.toml (stk_8f3c6a2e).`}
    lang="text"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <p>Two files appear on disk:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <code>.stack.toml</code> — committed. The <em>shape</em> of your stack.
    </li>
    <li>
      <code>.stack.local.toml</code> — gitignored automatically. Your
      project_id and per-developer instance data.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Stack also appends <code>.stack.local.toml</code> to your <code>.gitignore</code>
    so you can't accidentally commit it. See the <a href="/docs/config/">config
    reference</a> for the full schema.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Add your first service</h2>
  <p>Let's wire up Supabase — the most interesting one, because it has a full
    upstream provisioning flow plus an MCP server.</p>

  <Code
    code={`stack add supabase`}
    lang="bash"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <p>Stack will:</p>

  <ol>
    <li>Pop a browser window for Supabase OAuth (PKCE — no secrets pasted).</li>
    <li>Create a new project in your default org.</li>
    <li>Generate a DB password, store it in Phantom.</li>
    <li>Fetch the anon + service-role keys and route them into Phantom.</li>
    <li>Add a <code>supabase</code> MCP entry to <code>.mcp.json</code> scoped to the new project.</li>
    <li>Write the service into <code>.stack.toml</code> + <code>.stack.local.toml</code>.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>You'll see something like:</p>

  <Code
    code={`┌  stack add supabase
│
◇  ● supabase (abcdefghijklmnop) · 3 secrets · mcp wired
│
└  ✓ supabase is live.`}
    lang="text"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>No Phantom prompts?</strong> Good. Stack wrote the secrets through
    Phantom's programmatic API — you'll never see the real values. See <a
    href="/docs/phantom/">Phantom</a> for the full story.
  </div>

  <h2>5. Sanity-check with <code>doctor</code></h2>
  <p>
    Before you move on, verify everything is reachable. <code>stack doctor</code>
    hits each configured provider and confirms the stored credentials still
    work:
  </p>

  <Code
    code={`stack doctor`}
    lang="bash"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <Code
    code={`┌  stack doctor
│
◇  ● supabase (218ms)
│
└  All services healthy.`}
    lang="text"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <p>
    Run this before deploys, after a stale laptop comes out of a drawer, or any
    time something feels off. In CI, use <code>stack doctor --json</code> —
    exit code <code>0</code> if healthy, <code>1</code> if any service fails.
    See <a href="/docs/ci/">CI integration</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Run your app with secrets injected</h2>
  <p>
    Instead of <code>bun dev</code>, run <code>stack exec -- bun dev</code>.
    Phantom's proxy injects real secret values for any <code>phm_</code> tokens
    at the network layer:
  </p>

  <Code
    code={`stack exec -- bun dev`}
    lang="bash"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <p>
    Your app boots with <code>SUPABASE_URL</code>, <code>SUPABASE_ANON_KEY</code>,
    and <code>SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY</code> available in <code>process.env</code>
    — without any plaintext secret ever touching disk.
  </p>

  <h2>What now?</h2>

  <div class="not-prose mt-6 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
    <a href="/docs/cli/" class="docs-card group">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-1 group-hover:text-magenta-200 transition-colors">
        CLI reference
      </h3>
      <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-400 leading-relaxed">
        Every command, flag, and default. Bookmark-worthy.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a href="/docs/providers/" class="docs-card group">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-1 group-hover:text-magenta-200 transition-colors">
        Providers
      </h3>
      <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-400 leading-relaxed">
        The 29 curated providers — what each wires and where its dashboard is.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a href="/docs/templates/" class="docs-card group">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-1 group-hover:text-magenta-200 transition-colors">
        Templates
      </h3>
      <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-400 leading-relaxed">
        Five opinionated starter stacks — the "SaaS in a box" ones.
      </p>
    </a>
    <a href="/docs/mcp/" class="docs-card group">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-1 group-hover:text-magenta-200 transition-colors">
        MCP in Claude Code
      </h3>
      <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-400 leading-relaxed">
        Drive Stack from Claude / Cursor / Windsurf via MCP tools.
      </p>
    </a>
  </div>
</Docs>
